# Wave API Configuration
#
# Wave uses OAuth 2.0. From your Wave Developer App you can obtain a
# "Full Access Token" (an access_token + refresh_token pair scoped to your
# own businesses). Provide all four values below so the server can
# automatically refresh the access token when it expires (~1 week TTL).
#
# Developer portal: https://developer.waveapps.com/
# OAuth guide:      https://developer.waveapps.com/hc/en-us/articles/360019493652-OAuth-Guide

WAVE_CLIENT_ID=your_wave_client_id_here
WAVE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_wave_client_secret_here
WAVE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_wave_access_token_here
WAVE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_wave_refresh_token_here

# Optional: Specify a business ID if you have multiple businesses.
# If not provided, the server will auto-detect (single-business accounts)
# or you can choose one at runtime via the set_business tool.
# WAVE_BUSINESS_ID=your_business_id_here
